
[1]stipe

   STIPE, n. [L.; Gr., a stake.] In botany, the base of a frond; or a
   species of stem passing into leaves, or not distinct from the leaf. The
   stem of a fungus is also called stipe. The word is also used for the
   filament or slender stalk which supports the pappus or down, and
   connects it with the seed.
